===Article===
'''þe'''
* obsolete spelling of [[the]]
:'''Quotations'''
:*'''1431''': A rem' that William Baker, [[Pewtrer]], & John Hetheman [made] the first day of May, þ<sup>e</sup> [[ʒere]] of [[kynge]] herry [[þe]] vj<sup>e</sup>, after [[þe]] [[conquest]] x<sup>e</sup>. &mdash; Henry Littlehales (editor), ''The Medieval Records of a London City Church'', page 26.


==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*þa-'', from Indo-European ''*to, *te''.

